org.knime.core.node.workflow

Class WorkflowContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.node.workflow.WorkflowContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Externalizable, Serializable

    public final class WorkflowContext
extends Object
implements Externalizable
    This class holds information about the context in which a workflows currently resides. It includes information such as the current workflow directory or the ID of the user executing the workflow. Instances must be created via the WorkflowContext.Factory since the workflow context is purely read-only. This class is not intended to be used by clients.
    Since:
    4.4
    Author:
    Thorsten Meinl, KNIME.com Zurich, Switzerland
    See Also:
